  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed development, by virtue of the loss of rear garden space, results in the over development of the rear garden and a loss openness to the rear of the dwelling, and in combination with its inappropriate and out of keeping materiality for its garden setting, causes harm to the character and appearance of the host property, adjoining properties and the South Hampstead Conservation Area, contrary to policy D1 (Design), D2 (Heritage), and A3 (Biodiversity) of the Camden Local Plan 2017.",
    "Reason : 2 - In the absence of a Flood Risk and Drainage Assessment, required due to the increase of impermeable surfacing within a Local Flood Risk Zone, the Applicant has failed to demonstrate that the proposal would not increase flood risk at the site or on adjoining site within an identified Local Flood Risk Zone, contrary to policy CC3 (Water and Flooding) of the Camden Local Plan 2017."
